        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 4:07PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 407 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of White Sulphur Springs, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lennep.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
central Montana.</instruction>
